# JONBEATZ.DEV — Core Rules

This is the **standalone** red command-center site (`jonbeatz.dev`), split out of the
JonBeatz personal profile. It is its own self-contained Next.js + Three.js project.

## What this project IS

- A single-page, dark, cinematic portfolio/command-center site with a **red theme**
  and a **glow-beam hero portal** (the `dev` variant is the baked-in default).
- Self-contained: website code, UI/3D design skills, docs, dev/build/deploy/backup
  scripts, **OmniVoice (JARVIS) ritual voice**, and **project MCPs** all live here.

## What this project is NOT

- **Not** the personal JonBeatz profile. Do **not** add Telegram, DeepSeek/LiteLLM,
  ComfyUI, Google Workspace, or image-gen wiring here — those belong to
  `D:\Hermes\projects\JonBeatz`. (OmniVoice + MCPs ARE welcome here.)
- **Not** the gold `jon-beatz.com` site. That stays in the personal profile. This repo
  only ships `jonbeatz.dev` (red).

## Safety defaults

- **Environment:** Windows 10/11 **PowerShell**. No bash heredocs (`<<`).
- **Mem0:** scope is **`jonbeatz_dev`** (`qdrant_jonbeatz_dev`) only. Never write into
  `jonbeatz_personal` or any MSC store.
- **Secrets:** never commit `.env*`. Config template = `.env.local.example`.
- **UTF-8 / docs:** never bulk-rewrite `.md`/`.mdc` from PowerShell without `-Encoding UTF8`.
  Use `npm run version:sync` (Python) for README badges; run `npm run encoding:check`
  before doc commits.

## Variant mechanism

- Red is the **default** — `npm run dev` and `npm run build` produce the red site with
  the glow beam, no flags needed.
- Driven by `NEXT_PUBLIC_JB_VARIANT` (defaults to dev; set `"default"` for the legacy
  gold theme) + `JB_STATIC=1` for the static export. See `app/layout.tsx`,
  `app/page.tsx`, `components/ThreeBackground.tsx`.

